         <abstract id="aspace_6d46416427dc16a95d3a7eab6abd3ef3">Notebooks, loose notes, index cards, and printed materials kept by Gordon Hislop and relating to English poet and landscape gardener William Shenstone, circa 1909-1929. Materials--seemingly the result of an unpublished manuscript--include analyses of poems and correspondence (from Shenstone and other poets), as well as bibliographies on ballads and gardening in the 18th century.</abstract>
